comments: Jackson (IND) establishes himself in Young's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick.
Okongwu (ATL) legally contests Hield's (IND) jump shot attempt.
Mathurin (IND) and Hunter (ATL) both make clean contact with the ball as they pursue the rebound.
Hunter (ATL) swipes down and makes contact with Mathurin's (IND) right wrist as he pulls it away from the ball, which affects his ability to gather.
The ball touches the back of Hunter's (ATL) hand last before going out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to the Pacers.
During the inbound, Hunter (ATL) and Hield (IND) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Hunter (ATL) moves slightly toward Hield (IND) as he squeezes over the pick and marginal contact occurs as they briefly come together.
During the drive, Murray (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position alongside Mathurin (IND) as Mathurin loses control of the ball on his gather.
Collins (ATL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Mathurin (IND) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Okongwu's (ATL) arm.
Jackson (IND) and Okongwu (ATL) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs as they jostle for rebounding position.
Hunter (ATL) grasps Brissett's (IND) jersey and immediately releases it as marginal contact occurs during the pursuit of the rebound.
Okongwu (ATL) and Jackson (IND) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Hunter (ATL) is not vertical when he initiates contact with Mathurin's (IND) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Mathurin (IND) goes to, not through, Young's (ATL) space and marginal contact occurs as the two come together during the screen. Young's reaction is not commensurate with the level of contact.
Collins (ATL) is in the lane for about three seconds when he receives the pass and starts his upward shooting motion.
Jackson (IND) legally contests Collins' (ATL) shot near the basket.
Jackson (IND) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
The loose ball ricochets off Mathurin's (IND) leg and goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly maintained by the Hawks.
Nembhard (IND) is slightly late to establish himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs as they briefly come together during the dribble hand-off pick.
Okongwu (ATL) initiates contact with Hield's (IND) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt. Any contact with the ball by Collins (ATL), occurs simultaneous to the illegal arm contact by Okongwu.
McConnell (IND) avoids making contact with Murray's (ATL) body as he contests the jump shot attempt.

Brissett (IND) rests his hand on Collins' (ATL) shoulder and marginal contact occurs during the putback tip shot attempt. After review, the basket is counted and there is 0.7 seconds left on the game clock.

Okongwu (ATL) elevates and marginal contact occurs as his off-arm grazes Smith's (IND) face simultaneous to Hunter (ATL) cleanly deflecting away the inbounds pass.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
